description._content: He comes from a tiny village near Meerut. His father ekes out a living, making funeral articles for Hindus and Muslims alike. But for 2 months in a year, he moves to Delhi with his father, to help him make Dussehra effigies. These two months of backbreaking work will generate enough income to see the family of seven through. He sleeps on the pavement and works without a shirt. Yet he has a smile on his face. He is my hero.
